description:
This is a 2 panel mosaic of the Iris Nebula and the Ghost Nebula shot LRGB from two different locations. The left panel was shot from Fall Creek Falls State Park in Spencer, TN in 2016 and the right panel was shot from the Marathon Motel and RV Park in Marathon, TX in 2017. 

Software used to capture image:
Sequence Generator Pro
PHD2

Software used to edit:
PixInsight
Photoshop

Total Data gathered:
(82) Lum @ 600secs - 1x1
(35) R @ 600secs - 1x1
(36) G @ 600secs - 1x1
(31) B @ 600secs - 1x1
(8) Lum @ 60secs - 1x1
(8) R @ 60secs - 1x1
(8) G @ 60secs - 1x1
(8) B @ 60secs - 1x1

Camera : ATIK 383L+ Mono
Telescope: William Optics GT102 W_0.8x Reducer Flattener
Mount: AP Mach1GTO
imaging_telescopes: William Optics GT102 102mm f/6.9 Apo Refractor
title: The Iris Nebula and the Ghost Nebula
